ate governance. Covers the history and basics of Islamic finance, and provides insight into current conditions and future landscape; Explores regulatory framework, including opportunities and challenges for the industry's development and mainstreaming; Presents an approach to developing a systemic Shari'a governance framework to govern operations in the Islamic finance industry.--</subfield><subfield code="c">Edited summary from book.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">57</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Finance</subfield><subfield code="x">Religious aspects</subfield><subfield code="x">Islam.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Banks and banking</subfield><subfield code="x">Religious aspects</subfield><subfield code="x">Islam.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Financial institutions</subfield><subfield code="x">Religious aspects</subfield><subfield code="x">Islam.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Finance (Islamic law)</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Finance</subfield><subfield code="z">Islamic countries.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Economics</subfield><subfield code="x">Religious aspects</subfield><subfield code="x">Islam.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="700"><subfield code="a">Grais, Wafik,</subfield><subfield code="d">1949- ,</subfield><subfield code="e">author.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="830"><subfield code="a">Wiley finance series.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="4" ind2="0" tag="856"><subfield code="3">MacEwan University Access</subfield><subfield code="u">http://ezproxy.macewan.ca/login?url=http://library.books24x7.com/library.asp?^B&amp;bookid=63607</subfield><subfield code="z